An Ebute Meta Magistratesâ€™ Court on Monday ordered that 34-year-old Ndubuisi Ugo remanded following his arraignment for allegedly hiring an assassin for a 33-year-old man. Magistrate Tolu Agbona ordered that the case file be sent to the Lagos State Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP) for advice. He adjourned till July 27. Prosecuting Inspector A. Raphael said the defendant hired an assassin to kill one Mr Ohneoka Oderhowo. He said the defendant committed the offence on May 17 at 3, Atunbi Christ Street, Tedo-Muwo, Ojo.